# this is a comment in Relax NG. 
start = root
root = element root {title, chapter+}
title = element title {text}
chapter = element chapter {n, heading, p+}
p = element p {n, mixed{ (date | time | q)*}} 
# mixed syntax example with lots of flexiblity. Read from the inside out.
# The "or" pipes | and parentheses create a series of options. 
# Putting the repetition indicator *outside* the parentheses means 
# that Relax NG gives you your choice of *any* of these three, zero or more times. 
